&quot;Just playing devil&#x27;s advocate here.&quot;
Not sure what you&#x27;re getting out of that, but I&#x27;m happy to play along :-)<p>&quot;you suggest people waste: - a lot of their own time&quot;
I wouldn&#x27;t call it &quot;wasting time&quot; if it gets you the result you want.<p>&quot;even though you have nothing in common with them&quot;
Being startup founders is already having a lot in common.<p>&quot;All you want is a backhanded intro&quot;
I wouldn&#x27;t do any of this in a backhanded way, founders will smell it. Be transparent and upfront.<p>&quot;Only so that the investor will get 2-3 emails&quot;
The question was how to get warm introductions... these are warm introductions :)<p>&quot;from founders who really know nothing about you other than what they found out in a 10 minute phone call&quot;
... or from follow up interactions you&#x27;ve had with them after that initial 10 minute phone call...<p>&quot;Don&#x27;t you think that system is broken?&quot;
Nope :) I think it&#x27;s an imperfect system - but then everything in the real world is.
